## Agent Doctor Mission Complete — 2026-02-27

### Diagnosis

**ROOT CAUSE**: All 9 agents failed because GNU `timeout` (coreutils) was not installed on macOS. Every agent invoked via `run-ctem-swarm.sh` hit `timeout: command not found` and exhausted 3 retry attempts. Coreutils was auto-installed at 10:41, but subsequent runs were interrupted (SIGINT).

### Fixes Applied

1. **`scripts/run-ctem-swarm.sh`** — Hardened timeout resolution:
   - Prefer `gtimeout` (canonical macOS coreutils name) over `timeout`
   - Verify command actually WORKS (`$cmd 0.1 true`) not just EXISTS (`command -v`)
   - Loop through candidates instead of fragile if/elif

2. **Environment verified healthy**: timeout, gtimeout, claude, node all available. 720GB disk free. All directories exist. All 15 agent YAML files valid. All 8 CTEM+ scanner engines intact (5,134 LOC).

